HEADWORD: Slightness
<hw>Slight"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
slight; slenderness; feebleness; superficiality; also, formerly,
negligence; indifference; disregard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slighty</ent>⟦br⟧
